## Installation

This project uses [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) for Python and dependency
management.

Install uv if needed:

```shell
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh
```

Then install Python and project dependencies:

```shell
uv python install {{ python_version }}
uv sync --all-groups
```

## Development

The `Makefile` provides shortcuts for the common development workflow:

```shell
make install      # Install dependencies
make lint         # Run pre-commit hooks
make typecheck    # Run BasedPyright
make test         # Run tests with coverage
make build        # Build the package
make clean        # Remove generated local artifacts
```

Install pre-commit hooks once after cloning:

```shell
uv run pre-commit install
```

Useful direct commands:

```shell
uv run pytest
uv run pre-commit run --all-files
uv add package_name
uv add --dev package_name
```

## Publishing

Releases are published to the GitLab PyPI package registry by GitLab CI. The flow is
tag-driven:

1. Push a version tag such as `v0.1.0`.
2. GitLab CI runs linting and tests.
3. The `pypi` job builds and uploads the package.
4. The `release` job creates a GitLab Release.

Create a release tag:

```shell
git status
git tag vX.Y.Z
git push origin vX.Y.Z
```

For private packages, configure access to the GitLab package registry with a deploy
token, personal access token, or CI job token.

